{"id":"host-of-heaven","term":"Host of heaven","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>The sun, moon, and stars are so designated (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 2:1\">Gen. 2:1</a>). When the Jews fell into idolatry they worshipped these (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Deuteronomy 4:19\">Deut. 4:19</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Kings 17:16\">2 Kings 17:16</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Kings 21:3\">21:3</a>,<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Kings 21:5\">5</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Kings 23:5\">23:5</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Jeremiah 19:13\">Jer. 19:13</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Zephaniah 1:5\">Zeph. 1:5</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Acts 7:42\">Acts 7:42</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Genesis 2:1","Deuteronomy 4:19","2 Kings 17:16","2 Kings 21:3","2 Kings 21:5","2 Kings 23:5","Jeremiah 19:13","Zephaniah 1:5","Acts 7:42"]}